Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winner s Of A Race Other Than Claiming, Or Starter At A Mile Or Over Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000 (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $16,000 Or Less In Their Last 3 Starts Preferred)(Horses Entered For The Allowance Are Preferred). (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CALIFORNIA BAY got brushed and crowded into the first turn, traveled in mid-pack on the inside, ran up behind rivals and had to pause on the backstretch, moved out three wide on the far turn, angled out in the in the lane and rallied to overhaul the runner-up. DISCRETIONARY DAY dueled for the lead from inside then ceded command into the backstretch, switch out and pressed up the backstretch, dueled into the lane, took over in upper stretch and got run down by the winner late. BRAVESTONE was off a bit slow to begin, taken back to avoid a tight spot between runners, settled in the two path, drew closer up the backstretch, gained three then four wide on the far turn, rallied in the lane but was outkicked by the top pair. FORE FLAG stalked on the inside, had to pause when running up on heels early on the backstretch, continued to stalk up the inside, asked left handed leaving the far turn, lacked room in upper stretch, tipped out and finished willingly. TALKLESSWORKMORE tracked from the rail position, waited for room on the far turn, lacked room from upper to midstretch and was ridden out once clear in the final sixteenth. DOS VICIOS broke in and bumped rival, tracked two wide outside a rival, raced between foes then outside a rival on the second bend, lacked room in upper stretch, angled out and kept on trying to the wire. ALPINE THUNDER hard to load prior to the start, got knocked into inner rival at the start, trailed two wide early, spun three wide into the lane, moved out wide in the stretch and showed a mild response to improve position. MYSTIC FLYER dueled for command from outside then cleared leaving the clubhouse turn and moved inside, pressure up the backstretch, dueled into the lane, fought to the sixteenth pole and weakened late. SYNTACTIC brushed inner rival into the first turn, settled two wide, saved ground through the far turn and failed to menace. HACKING IT UP stalked in the two path, chased three wide into the lane and weakened. DON'TTHINKJUSTDOIT bumped from outside at the start, raced on the inside near the back, trailed around the far turn, eased in the lane and walked off. DUE TO TIMER MALFUNCTION THE FIRST QUARTER WAS HAND-TIMED.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: COFFEE IN BED stalked from inside, launched a bid inside the leaders and gained the lead at the quarter pole, fought with CLIQUISH in upper stretch, put that rival away at the eighth pole under hand urging and was ridden out to the wire. CLIQUISH tracked four then three wide around the first turn, went two wide into the second bend, bid four, five, then three deep on the far turn, fought with the winner to upper stretch, was no match for that rival in the furlong grounds but was clearly second best. LIBERAL LADY attended the pace three deep, vied three then four deep on the far turn, could not match strides with the leaders at the top of the lane and weakened in the late stages. KEEN LADY settled off the rail and angled in around the clubhouse turn, continued to save ground through the far turn and passed tired rivals. BLUE WILDCAT took control early from inside, dueled up the backstretch, drifted out and had to take hold briefly at the quarter pole, chased two wide into the lane and weakened. VITALERA (CHI) raced up close two to three wide, confronted the leader and dueled up the backstretch, vied between on the far turn, got put in a bit tight at the quarter pole and faded.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ANNIE'S JOY stalked on the inside, drew closer along the rail on the far turn, tipped out and challenged from outside with a furlong left to run, dueled with RUGELACH in the final sixteenth and drove past. RUGELACH brushed rival at the start, sped to the front in the two path then moved inside, drew away with three furlongs left to run, held a diminished lead entering the lane, responded when pressured by ANNIE'S JOY at the eighth pole and yielded grudgingly in the end. PRECOCIOUS TIMES traveled in mid-pack, saved ground through both turns, moved out in the lane and finished willingly for a clear third. FIRSTTIMEINFOREVER had to steady when rival came over early, traveled outside a rival towards the rear, ridden along while tipping three wide on the far turn, chased two wide into the drive and could not rally. RUFF RIDE broke in and bumped, raced on the inside near the back in the early going, went two wide into the far turn, angled out to the four path midway around the far turn, spun three wide into the lane and needed to find more. NOKIE trailed on the inside early, angled three wide approaching the quarter pole, had to steady entering the stretch and could not regain momentum. COURT SNORT settled off the pace and moved to the rail, saved ground through the far turn and lacked a rally. JORDAN got bumped leaving the gate, was closest in pursuit from the two path, coaxed along into the far turn, dropped back around that bend, eased in the lane and walked off.

AVOIR stalked off the rail then moved inside, saved ground through the turn, finished willingly in the drive but could not get by UFFDA for second. LAUDATORY bumped leaving the gate, raced at the back two wide into the turn, spun three wide into the stretch and showed a mild response when called upon. DISCREPANCY broke in and bumped, traveled in mid-pack three deep, chased two wide into the lane and lacked a rally. CERTITUDE (FR) brushed leaving the gate, became rank briefly early, traveled in mid-pack on the inside into the turn, saved ground to the stretch and lacked the needed response. RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOOD WITH PEOPLE closest in pursuit from inside into the turn, reeled in the leader while shifted to the two path on the turn, drew alongside and dueled into the stretch, put away KINGDOM HEART approaching the eighth pole and held under a strong drive. ESCAPE ROUTE bumped leaving the gate, sat off the pace outside a rival, rounded the bend three wide, put in a late bid but ran out of time. RACE.RACE_TEXT: Swingtime S. SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 9 1M Turf CR: 99. Stakes Purse 80000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A SWEEPSTAKES OF $60,000 AT ONE MILE OR OVER OTHER THAN STATE BRED IN 2023. FREE nominations close Friday, September 22, 2023, closed with 19. $1,600 Supplementary nominations close at time of entry. All horses to pay $600 to enter and an additional $600 to start with $80,000 added. The added monies and all fees to be divided 60% to the winner, 20% to second, 12% to third, 6% to fourth and 2% to fifth. Three-Year-Olds 122 lbs. Older 12 6 lbs. Non-Winners of a Sweepstakes at One Mile or Over allowed 2 lbs. Non-Winners of Two races other than Maiden, Claiming or Starter at One Mile or Over allowed 4 lbs. (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LUCKY GIRL (IRE) tucked inside racing near the back early, ridden along and angled three wide midway around the far turn, steered out further in the stretch, unleashed a rally under right handed encouragement and got up in the closing moments. FREEDOM FLYER tracked outside a rival off the pace, gained along the inside then two wide on the far turn, bid three deep in upper stretch, took over midstretch and got run down by LUCKY GIRL (IRE) in the final strides. UNBRIDLED MARY was closest in pursuit in the two path then moved inside, reeled in the leader on the far turn and confronted HAMWOOD FLIER (IRE) entering the stretch, took over shortly after, relinquished the lead to FREEDOM FLYER midstretch and kept on to hold the show. EDDIE'S NEW DREAM settled along the inside, hugged the rail to the stretch, moved out in the lane, bid inside rivals approaching the sixteenth pole but needed to find more late. OAKHURST taken back to last early and steered to the inside, trailed to the rail turn, went between rivals then two wide around that bend, moved out in the lane and finished evenly late. PRESENT MOMENT (IRE) traveled in the two path between rivals around the clubhouse turn off the pace, continued between into the far turn, asked two wide at the quarter pole and failed to respond. UNA CHIQUITITA (CHI) was off slow to begin, pulled along the inside early, saved ground to the stretch and was not a factor. HAMWOOD FLIER (IRE) broke through the gate and had to be reloaded, cleared quickly and crossed over, opened up a comfortable lead early, continued well clear into the far turn, saw her lead diminishing through the far turn and clung to short lead entering the lane, was overtaken shortly after and retreated in the final furlong. ANKYRAH tracked three deep well out of range in the early going, remained three wide into the far turn, bothered briefly by rival coming out approaching the quarter pole and weakened in the stretch run.
